schema.description: The currently desired state of the device.

payload.description:
An application-specific JSON object. HERE Tracking doesn't read this object but
you can use it to pass information to other applications. The maximum size is 1000B.

system.description:
Contains values for the device configuration. HERE Tracking uses these values
for various application flows.

Unlike the payload object, HERE Tracking reads the contents of the system object.

detectOutliers.description: A boolean value that sets outlier detection on/off

disableTracking.description: Tracking can be disabled and enabled by defining disableTracking object. In order to disable tracking, you must at least provide the begin time of the disabling period and define either position or sensor properties you want to disable. You can also disable both position and sensors at the same time. By default tracking is enabled.

periods.description: Define begin and end of the disabling period. All trace points with timestamp that falls between begin and end times will be disabled according to the settings defined in the position and sensors properties.

begin.description:
Milliseconds elapsed since 1 January 1970 00:00:00 UTC

Begin time of the tracking disabling period.

Begin must be smaller than end. Begin must be greater or equal to current time.
Begin can be set without end. If there exists already end time which is earlier
than given new begin time, the existing end time will be deleted.

end.description:
Milliseconds elapsed since 1 January 1970 00:00:00 UTC

End time of the tracking disabling period.

End must be greater than begin. End must be greater or equal to current time.
End can be set without begin if begin is already set.

periods.title: Array of periods

position.description: Define position methods to be disabled

oneOf.description: All positioning data the device sends will be removed before further processing. No geofence and location events will be generated
oneOf.title: all positioning

items.description: The items specified in the position array will be removed from the ingestion scan object before further processing. Position may be resolved by the remaining scan properties. Some geofence and location events may be generated.

oneOf.description: By setting the position property empty string, all positioning data will be re-enabled during the disabling period.
oneOf.title: re-enable

oneOf.description: All sensor data the device sends will be removed before further processing. No sensor events will be generated.
oneOf.title: all sensors

items.description: The items specified in the sensors array will be removed from the ingestion system.reportedSensorData object before further processing. Sensor events will not be generated for the disabled sensors.

oneOf.description: By setting the sensors property empty string, all sensors data will be re-enabled during the disabling period.
oneOf.title: re-enable

lastModifiedGeofenceTimestamp.description:
Milliseconds elapsed since 1 January 1970 00:00:00 UTC.

The time of the last update to geofences that device is associated
with. This value is zero when device hasn't yet been associated with
any geofence. This is set by HERE Tracking when any geofences
associated with the device is modified or removed. Also adding and
removing geofence associations update this value.

rate.description: This can be used to specify the rates at which the device performs certain tasks.

distanceM.description: The device should send an update if it moves more than this distance in meters

sampleMs.description: The rate at which to sample signals in milliseconds

sendMs.description: The rate at which to send sample results in milliseconds

alertAccelerationGMax.description: A maximum threshold value for acceleration in g-force.

alertAccelerationGMin.description: A minimum threshold value for acceleration in g-force.

alertBatteryLevelPMax.description: A maximum threshold value for battery level in percent.

alertBatteryLevelPMin.description: A minimum threshold value for battery level in percent.

alertPressureHpaMax.description: A maximum threshold value for pressure in hectopascal.

alertPressureHpaMin.description: A minimum threshold value for pressure in hectopascal.

alertRelativeHumidityMax.description: A maximum threshold value for relative humidity in percent.

alertRelativeHumidityMin.description: A minimum threshold value for relative humidity in percent.

alertTemperatureCMax.description: A maximum threshold value for temperature in celcius.

alertTemperatureCMin.description: A minimum threshold value for temperature in celcius.

alertTiltDegreeMax.description: A maximum threshold value for tilt in degrees.

alertTiltDegreeMin.description: A minimum threshold value for tilt in degrees.

isAttachAlertEnabled.description: True if attach sensor alert in device is enabled.

isTamperAlertEnabled.description: True if tamper sensor alert in device is enabled.

stateVersion.description: The version of the state of a device. This should be incremented only by HERE Tracking.

syncGeofences.description: A boolean value that sets efficient geofencing on/off

timestamp.description:
Milliseconds elapsed since 1 January 1970 00:00:00 UTC.

The time of the last update to the desired state. This is set by HERE Tracking
when an update is written to the desired state.

payload.description:
An application-specific JSON object. HERE Tracking doesn't read this object but
you can use it to pass information to other applications. The maximum size is 1000B.

system.description:
Contains values for the device configuration. HERE Tracking uses these values
for various application flows.

Unlike the payload object, HERE Tracking reads the contents of the system object.

detectOutliers.description: A boolean value that sets outlier detection on/off

disableTracking.description: Tracking can be disabled and enabled by defining disableTracking object. In order to disable tracking, you must at least provide the begin time of the disabling period and define either position or sensor properties you want to disable. You can also disable both position and sensors at the same time. By default tracking is enabled.

periods.description: Define begin and end of the disabling period. All trace points with timestamp that falls between begin and end times will be disabled according to the settings defined in the position and sensors properties.

begin.description:
Begin time of the tracking disabling period.

Begin must be smaller than end. Begin must be greater or equal to current time.
Begin can be set without end. If there exists already end time which is earlier
than given new begin time, the existing end time will be deleted.

end.description:
End time of the tracking disabling period.

End must be greater than begin. End must be greater or equal to current time.
End can be set without begin if begin is already set.

periods.title: Array of periods

position.description: Define position methods to be disabled

oneOf.description: All positioning data the device sends will be removed before further processing. No geofence and location events will be generated
oneOf.title: all positioning

items.description: The items specified in the position array will be removed from the ingestion scan object before further processing. Position may be resolved by the remaining scan properties. Some geofence and location events may be generated.

oneOf.description: By setting the position property empty string, all positioning data will be re-enabled during the disabling period.
oneOf.title: re-enable

oneOf.description: All sensor data the device sends will be removed before further processing. No sensor events will be generated.
oneOf.title: all sensors

items.description: The items specified in the sensors array will be removed from the ingestion system.reportedSensorData object before further processing. Sensor events will not be generated for the disabled sensors.

oneOf.description: By setting the sensors property empty string, all sensors data will be re-enabled during the disabling period.
oneOf.title: re-enable

lastModifiedGeofenceTimestamp.description:
The time of the last update to geofences that device is associated
with. This value is zero when device hasn't yet been associated with
any geofence. This is set by HERE Tracking when any geofences
associated with the device is modified or removed. Also adding and
removing geofence associations update this value.

rate.description: This can be used to specify the rates at which the device performs certain tasks.

distanceM.description: The device should send an update if it moves more than this distance in meters

sampleMs.description: The rate at which to sample signals in milliseconds

sendMs.description: The rate at which to send sample results in milliseconds

alertAccelerationGMax.description: A maximum threshold value for acceleration in g-force.

alertAccelerationGMin.description: A minimum threshold value for acceleration in g-force.

alertBatteryLevelPMax.description: A maximum threshold value for battery level in percent.

alertBatteryLevelPMin.description: A minimum threshold value for battery level in percent.

alertPressureHpaMax.description: A maximum threshold value for pressure in hectopascal.

alertPressureHpaMin.description: A minimum threshold value for pressure in hectopascal.

alertRelativeHumidityMax.description: A maximum threshold value for relative humidity in percent.

alertRelativeHumidityMin.description: A minimum threshold value for relative humidity in percent.

alertTemperatureCMax.description: A maximum threshold value for temperature in celcius.

alertTemperatureCMin.description: A minimum threshold value for temperature in celcius.

alertTiltDegreeMax.description: A maximum threshold value for tilt in degrees.

alertTiltDegreeMin.description: A minimum threshold value for tilt in degrees.

isAttachAlertEnabled.description: True if attach sensor alert in device is enabled.

isTamperAlertEnabled.description: True if tamper sensor alert in device is enabled.

syncGeofences.description: A boolean value that sets efficient geofencing on/off

accuracy.description: Uncertainty circle radius in meters (degree of confidence according to the 'confidence' parameter).

alt.description: Altitude in meters (referenced to the WGS-84 ellipsoid) negative or positive.

altaccuracy.description: Uncertainty of the altitude estimate in meters (degree of confidence according to the 'confidence' parameter).

confidence.description: Confidence level in percent for the accuracy/uncertainty. If not specified, the default is 68 (this corresponds to a 68% probability that the true position is within the accuracy/uncertainty radius of the position; the higher the number, the greater the confidence level).

floor.description: The building where the measurements were taken

id.description: The building id

lng.description: Longitude in WGS-84 format, decimal representation ranging from -180 to 180.

speed.description: GPS/GNSS speed of the device (m/s). You must specify a value for this item when you specify a value for heading.

than given new begin time, the existing end time will be deleted.

end.description:

The parameter `value` refers to the `measure` parameter.

* `measure`: `duration` => `value`: duration of the event in seconds over the time frame
* `measure`: `occurrence` => `value`: number of event periods during the time frame
* `measure`: `day`, => `value`: number of days when the event happened over time frame
* `measure`: `asset`, => `value`: number of assets for which the event happened over the time frame

When `value` is provided with `timestamp`, the time frame is the specified interval.
When value is provided with `trackingId` or `geofenceId`, the time frame is the whole report start-end period.

Additionally, if `method` parameter is given, the `value` represents
average/cumulative/percentage of the measured value.

eventType.description:
Type of the event. Event types depend on the data the device sends.

Sensors that report numerical measurement data (battery, humidity, pressure and temperature)
report values inside or outside the rule range. Therefore the event generated by the crossing
of the rule limits causes BELOW_RANGE, IN_RANGE and ABOVE_RANGE event types.

Sensors that report boolean data (attach, tamper) generate events when they transition from
a state to another. When a device previously reported false but then reported true value for
the sensor generates a FALSE_TO_TRUE event (and vice versa for the TRUE_TO_FALSE event).

Sensors that report data when a monitored event occurs (e.g. the tracker was dropped) generate
events of type EVENT. They are not dependent on previous values sent by the device.

Events of type INSIDE_GEOFENCE and OUTSIDE_GEOFENCE are generated when the device enters or exits
geofence associated to the device.

Events of type DWELLING_STARTED are generated when the time a device has
spent inside an associated geofence exceeds the threshold duration. DWELLING_ENDED events
are generated when the dwelling period ends.

Events of type DETENTION_STARTED are generated when the device has been continuously
stationary longer than the threshold duration. DETENTION_ENDED events will be generated
when the device starts moving again.

Events of type UTILIZED are generated when the device starts moving.
UNUTILIZED events are generated when the device stops moving and also has been continuously
stationary longer than the threshold duration.

Events of type OVERSTOCK, NORMAL_VOLUME and UNDERSTOCK are generated when the number of assets
inside a geofence cross the minVolume and maxVolume thresholds of an associated stock rule.

initialState.description:
Initial state events are generated when the rule is evaluated for the first time in relation
to a device or a shipment. Initial state events represent the state where the device is
whereas the rest of the events represent a transition from a state to another.

All generic events are considered non-initial.

threshold.description:
Detention event is triggered when the asset has been continuously stationary longer
than the threshold duration.

Dwelling event is triggered when the asset has been continuously inside a geofence
longer than the threshold duration.

Utilization event is triggered when the asset starts moving
to indicate the asset is utilized, and also when the asset stops
moving and has been stationary longer than the threshold duration
to indicate the asset is unutilized.
